  "texts": [
    "However, in this case the phenomenon is no longer disinformation.)Veracity.",
    "Drawing on [42], we include three types of veracity of information: true, borderline, and false.",
    "By true information, we consider factually correct and verified content.",
    "The borderline category is an umbrella term for content that ranges from what is defined by PolitiFact's methodology from \"mostly true\" and \"half true\" to \"mostly false\", referring to the lack of clarification, vagueness, omission of details or \"important critical facts that would give a different impression\" [39].",
    "We suggest paying particular attention to the borderline category as it has been shown to have a substantial effect on beliefs in misinformation statements."
  ],
